WEBVTT

00:00.642 --> 00:04.307
This is Colossians chapter four, beginning verse two.

00:05.068 --> 00:10.255
Continue earnestly in prayer, being vigilant in it with thanksgiving.

00:11.818 --> 00:29.362
Meanwhile praying for also for us that God would open to us a door for the word to speak the mystery of Christ for which I am also in chains, that I may make it manifest as I ought to speak.

00:30.882 --> 00:35.868
walk in wisdom towards those who are outside, redeeming the time.

00:36.569 --> 00:44.459
Let your speech always be with grace, seasoned with salt, that you may know how you ought to answer each one.

00:44.499 --> 00:47.343
This is where God, for the people of God.

00:47.383 --> 00:49.666
Amen.

00:49.686 --> 00:51.949
May God add His blessing to the reading and His word.

00:52.189 --> 00:53.010
You may be seated.

01:00.290 --> 01:14.065
There is a passage in the New Testament that I have read and heard since I was young, very young, and I had trouble understanding it until very recently.

01:15.507 --> 01:25.618
I don't know if I'm slow or I just couldn't put the pieces together or it wasn't time for me to understand it, but sometimes, you know,

01:26.306 --> 01:29.690
You don't pick things up right away and you wonder why other people can.

01:29.990 --> 01:38.440
Well, I could explain the verse on one level, a passage, excuse me, but I had trouble explaining it on another.

01:38.480 --> 01:45.709
And I want to share with you, it's out of Matthew chapter 9, verses 14 through 17.

01:45.729 --> 01:47.371
I'm going to read that here in just a second.

01:47.851 --> 01:53.618
And what I want you to pay attention to is that Jesus has some parables in this real short passage.

01:54.114 --> 02:03.489
And I'm going to give you a basic understanding what I had of them and then tell you what God showed me throughout the last few weeks.

02:04.390 --> 02:14.747
The reason I tell you this is on one level, there's a meaning to the passage, but I wasn't satisfied because I thought there was more to it.

02:15.648 --> 02:18.292
And normally when you feel convicted, there's something more to it.

02:18.312 --> 02:19.314
There usually is.

02:19.618 --> 02:22.142
Usually the Holy Spirit promptings making us want to dig.

02:22.563 --> 02:25.067
I dug as much as I could still couldn't find that answer.

02:25.788 --> 02:31.838
So let me read for you Matthew 9 verses 14 through 17.

02:33.640 --> 02:43.396
Then the disciples of John came to him that is Jesus saying, why do we in the Pharisees fast often, but your disciples do not fast?

02:43.416 --> 02:44.658
And Jesus said to them,

02:45.730 --> 02:50.255
Can the friends of the bridegroom mourn as long as the bridegroom is with them?

02:51.217 --> 02:57.304
But the days will come when the bridegroom will be taken away from them and then they will fast.

02:57.324 --> 03:05.714
No one puts a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment, for the patch pulls away from the garment and the tear is made worse.

03:06.715 --> 03:11.681
Nor do they put new wine into old wineskins or else the wineskins break.

03:11.701 --> 03:15.506
The wine is spilled and the wineskins are ruined.

03:16.226 --> 03:20.951
But they put new wine into new wineskins and both are preserved.

03:22.873 --> 03:26.918
I think part of the reason I didn't understand the passages I've never used, the wineskin.

03:28.519 --> 03:29.220
Oh, new world.

03:30.041 --> 03:33.925
I didn't even know what they looked like or what they were about.

03:35.187 --> 03:41.393
And that's okay because the way I used to understand this parable didn't really matter that much.

03:42.895 --> 03:45.778
And by that I mean the intent of the parable

03:46.338 --> 03:51.806
is kind of clear to us by reading it, but in practicality for our life.

03:52.347 --> 03:53.368
How do we apply it?

03:54.650 --> 04:00.058
And what he's saying in this passage is, new and old don't mix.

04:03.943 --> 04:14.258
The unshrunk patch and the wine skin with wine always confuse me because I thought, well,

04:14.626 --> 04:15.547
Here's how we explain it.

04:15.567 --> 04:29.220
If we have a hole in a cotton shirt and we need to patch that hole, we don't have iron-on patches like my mom used to put on my jeans when I got holes in the knees, which made them look worse, rather have to hold.

04:29.561 --> 04:35.266
That's now modern design and style to have holes in the jean pre-made before you even buy them.

04:37.268 --> 04:38.309
I don't understand that.

04:38.349 --> 04:43.154
I keep thinking, you know, someone sold you a bill of goods, less material for more money.

04:44.290 --> 04:54.381
But the way I looked at it was that on a cotton shirt that you've worn a while, it's been washed, dried, washed, dried many times.

04:54.821 --> 04:56.964
It is shrunk to the size it's going to be.

04:57.765 --> 05:00.387
Now you might think, but it's still tighter than it used to be.

05:00.427 --> 05:01.849
That's a you, not the shirt.

05:04.171 --> 05:05.913
So if it has a hole, we need to patch it.

05:06.093 --> 05:14.002
And the way they did that back then was they would take a piece of cloth about the size of the hole and stitch it

05:14.530 --> 05:15.771
on the edges of the hole.

05:17.012 --> 05:26.141
Now, if that was a new piece of cotton material that they put in there and you wash it, that patch is going to shrink.

05:27.022 --> 05:32.267
And it's going to pull on those stitches on the edge of that hole and rip it further.

05:32.587 --> 05:34.449
That's what Jesus is talking about there.

05:35.050 --> 05:43.538
And so he said, you don't want to do that because the new cotton piece that you want to put into its place hasn't been washed.

05:47.394 --> 05:56.343
We are not going to be able to patch up sin with something new is what Jesus is saying in this passage, right?

05:57.544 --> 05:58.385
Well, I sin.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.166
I made a mistake.

05:59.186 --> 06:02.209
He said, OK, well, let's just put a patch on it.

06:02.229 --> 06:03.330
It doesn't work, does it?

06:03.850 --> 06:05.672
We can't patch sin.

06:06.493 --> 06:07.634
It just doesn't happen.

06:07.674 --> 06:09.216
That was something needs to happen.

06:09.756 --> 06:15.602
And so he talks about putting a new

06:16.066 --> 06:20.390
way of looking at things in this passage and we're going to get there.

06:23.053 --> 06:34.703
The reason the new patch doesn't match is you don't have an old piece laying around and you don't have a store that sells old pieces of material and I'll tell you why.

06:35.244 --> 06:38.687
Because everything over there that they needed to use was being used.

06:39.628 --> 06:44.873
You can't just go weave a small piece of material and then wear it out and put it on there.

06:44.893 --> 06:46.034
It just doesn't happen.

06:46.434 --> 06:47.596
That's not practical.

06:47.676 --> 06:48.938
It's not how they would do things.

06:49.639 --> 06:58.372
And there wasn't a store around where you could take it to a tailor to fix it either, because that kind of thing just didn't exist.

06:58.392 --> 07:09.810
The tailors in that time made brand new things not fix old things unless it was something that had come unstitched, but not a whole.

07:15.042 --> 07:24.313
Basically what this means and what it means for us is a hole in a garment means a garment will never be complete anymore.

07:25.394 --> 07:28.298
It cannot be completely what it was designed for.

07:28.798 --> 07:32.382
It's going to have an imperfection or a flaw and you can't fix it.

07:33.163 --> 07:34.705
And that's what Jesus is saying here.

07:38.510 --> 07:42.194
I saw children when I was in Malawi with holes in their garments.

07:44.482 --> 07:49.869
There just isn't enough clothes for them to have a second pair, so they had to wear the ones with holes in it.

07:50.270 --> 07:55.717
And because there's not enough clothes for them to have a second pair, there's not enough cloth anywhere to fix the one they have.

07:56.378 --> 07:57.600
So they wear what they had.

07:58.160 --> 08:05.110
When we passed out shirts to the different people, that was probably their second or maybe third shirt they possess.

08:06.932 --> 08:10.657
Because the clothes they wear, they have to wear over and over again.

08:10.697 --> 08:14.162
Because they can't afford new ones, they don't have a place

08:14.370 --> 08:20.818
to get new ones, and they don't have enough material to make one or to pay for a tailor to make them one.

08:21.839 --> 08:28.387
It is a very, very, very poverty-stricken places where we went, and I got to see that.

08:28.788 --> 08:30.410
As a matter of fact, this other's one little boy.

08:30.950 --> 08:33.313
He was wearing adult shorts at age four.

08:34.394 --> 08:38.439
They were huge on him, but he had clothes.

08:39.481 --> 08:43.986
I'm sure they were either hand-me-downs or pick-me-ups from somewhere.

08:47.010 --> 08:58.522
So when we talk about garments with holes, what Jesus is saying is, in a life of sin, once you have that first sin, you can't patch sin.

08:58.542 --> 09:00.023
It makes sense, right?

09:00.364 --> 09:10.214
And that's how I understood that verse, but there's a little more to it because he says, new wine won't go in old wine skins.

09:12.456 --> 09:14.418
This is a reference to us.

09:15.106 --> 09:17.249
It's also a reference to communion.

09:18.851 --> 09:23.598
We need a new body to house the new wine, which is His blood.

09:23.638 --> 09:30.527
Otherwise, we put the blood of Jesus into a sin-laden body which destroys and makes both unclean.

09:31.268 --> 09:34.393
That's what it says the old wineskin will be destroyed.

09:35.895 --> 09:41.042
Now, I was stuck with that interpretation just like that for many years.

09:42.658 --> 09:48.850
until about a month ago when I was at home taking one of those little portable community cups of waitress.

09:48.870 --> 09:54.662
I don't know if you've taken those very often, but sooner or later you get frustrated trying to open them.

09:56.525 --> 10:04.882
Seriously, you might get the bread out but you can't get the foil off the juice or you might get it such a way that you pull the

10:04.994 --> 10:07.136
Whole lid off and you get the juice but not the bread.

10:07.336 --> 10:09.138
Or you finally get it out and the bread's broken.

10:09.158 --> 10:10.860
You spilled the juice all over yourself.

10:11.200 --> 10:11.961
Very frustrating.

10:11.981 --> 10:14.764
Well, that particular day I had one of those problems.

10:16.085 --> 10:21.430
I pulled the lid thinking I was doing it right and the whole wafer and lid came off and I had the juice.

10:22.171 --> 10:28.017
And I said, well, Lord, rather, spill this juice, I'm going to take the juice and figure out how to get this thing separated.

10:28.057 --> 10:31.200
And I ended up with a wafer and about five parts, finally got it out.

10:31.961 --> 10:33.202
I almost had to use scissors.

10:33.954 --> 10:35.776
But that's how it sometimes is.

10:35.836 --> 10:41.463
But when that happened, I was concerned.

10:42.905 --> 10:44.027
Oh, I took the bread first.

10:45.869 --> 10:48.212
I mean, last, I took the juice first.

10:48.773 --> 10:50.094
Lord, does this matter?

10:50.114 --> 10:54.360
And almost immediately he gave me an answer.

10:55.301 --> 11:02.450
Why it took him years and years and years for me to figure out this wine skin and patch thing to what he was really saying

11:03.394 --> 11:06.757
The fuddles me when he gave me an answer to that and like immediately.

11:08.599 --> 11:23.193
Because if you look in the Passover cup that we symbolize, scripture says it comes after the meal, which is after the bread was broken, which happens at the beginning of the meal.

11:24.394 --> 11:33.362
So in that regard, if you're trying to understand the Passover meal or the Seder meal, which we're going to do, you cannot have the cup first

11:33.666 --> 11:36.430
that was representative of the one Jesus held.

11:36.811 --> 11:45.664
Now, in a Passover meal, there's four cups, and it's the third cup, the Jesus, blessed and said was his blood and a new covenant.

11:46.265 --> 12:00.626
So, there were other cups during the meal, but the third cup, the one that Jesus blessed and partook after the meal was over, was symbolic for what he was doing with it.

12:01.026 --> 12:08.955
So in terms of the meal itself and the symbolism of what the cup stood for, it mattered which cup.

12:09.615 --> 12:11.938
And in the order of the meal, it came after the bread.

12:11.978 --> 12:15.502
Did that matter though when we take communion?

12:16.383 --> 12:17.944
Some places only take bread.

12:18.985 --> 12:20.347
Some places do both.

12:20.387 --> 12:25.633
The answer was the verse in Matthew.

12:27.935 --> 12:30.578
He said to me, you can't

12:30.850 --> 12:35.194
put new wine into old wine skins.

12:36.276 --> 12:41.441
And immediately I began to understand what Jesus was talking about.

12:41.461 --> 12:52.112
In 2 Corinthians chapter 5 verse 17, we get an insight into how God works.

12:53.913 --> 12:55.815
Maybe you've heard this verse many times.

12:56.296 --> 12:58.418
It's one of those that people like to quote

12:59.138 --> 12:59.959
And it's a good one.

13:00.240 --> 13:00.881
It says this.

13:03.605 --> 13:08.673
Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation.

13:09.594 --> 13:11.337
Old things have passed away.

13:11.857 --> 13:15.203
Behold, all things have become new.

13:15.243 --> 13:20.130
And that word new, right?

13:20.491 --> 13:23.535
New wine, new wine skins, all things become new.

13:23.575 --> 13:25.298
And so,

13:25.474 --> 13:30.699
That's a clue to us that Jesus isn't just going to repair something, he's going to make a new.

13:32.601 --> 13:33.422
And that's a good thing.

13:36.265 --> 13:46.495
And one thing about communion when we partake, Jesus with the cup says, this is my blood poured out for you and for many for the forgiveness of sin.

13:46.515 --> 13:53.682
It's a new covenant, a new covenant that I ratify with my blood.

13:54.658 --> 14:09.018
We know that Jesus was establishing communion for us, but do we know really why it was so important that He said it was His blood poured out for us, not just on Calvary, but in communion as well.

14:09.118 --> 14:11.121
Why is the blood so important?

14:12.222 --> 14:20.694
And if you look in Leviticus there in chapter 17, the whole chapter talks about the significance of the blood.

14:22.196 --> 14:23.378
But in verse

14:23.906 --> 14:29.393
11, he says, the life of the flesh is in the blood.

14:29.433 --> 14:37.224
And I've given it to you upon the altar to make atonement for your souls.

14:39.868 --> 14:46.036
For it is the blood that makes atonement for the soul.

14:46.056 --> 14:50.642
So it takes blood to forgive sin, to wash it away.

14:51.778 --> 14:55.964
It is said in Scripture, a dead person has shed their blood.

14:56.044 --> 14:59.569
They no longer have to pay for the sin because they're shedding the blood dead.

15:00.931 --> 15:07.301
So death is required, not just, you know, bring your finger and drop some blood out and that covers your sin.

15:07.922 --> 15:11.407
By saying blood covers sin and makes atonement.

15:11.868 --> 15:16.274
It is of something that gives its life blood away, which means the thing must die.

15:20.034 --> 15:23.278
And he talks about it further in that chapter in Leviticus.

15:23.298 --> 15:34.853
He says, whatever man of the children of Israel or of the strangers, that's us, who dwell among you, who hunts and catches any animal or bird that may be eaten, he shall pour out its blood and cover it with dust.

15:35.614 --> 15:40.501
Listen to this, 14, for the blood is the life of all flesh.

15:41.062 --> 15:44.466
Its blood sustains its life.

15:47.074 --> 15:50.259
Therefore, I said to the children of Israel, you shall not eat the blood of any flesh.

15:50.299 --> 15:54.425
For the life of all flesh is its blood, wherever eats it will be cut off.

15:55.967 --> 16:00.353
It sounds like blood's pretty important if it sustains life, if it's what matters.

16:01.995 --> 16:10.788
And when we talk about this in Leviticus and the blood makes a toma for sin, I've known this for a long time.

16:11.870 --> 16:14.994
But I didn't make the comparison

16:16.674 --> 16:22.522
of that to communion and to the new one.

16:24.505 --> 16:27.710
Because I just couldn't make that jump.

16:30.233 --> 16:34.980
But I think you know this, a body without its blood in it is dead.

16:35.020 --> 16:37.123
Would you agree?

16:37.183 --> 16:39.246
You can't live without your blood.

16:40.027 --> 16:41.429
You suck all the blood out of your body.

16:41.469 --> 16:42.290
You are dead.

16:43.362 --> 16:48.909
That's just a fact and it's common knowledge and it's not something you go, oh how profound scripture said that.

16:49.349 --> 16:50.150
We know this.

16:50.331 --> 16:53.094
If you don't have any blood in you, you can't survive.

16:53.755 --> 16:56.919
And if you're very low on blood, you may not be able to survive as well.

16:57.760 --> 17:09.554
But so we know body without blood is dead, but blood without a body is just a sticky mess looking for

17:09.634 --> 17:18.888
a body to inhabit, like when we donate blood, that blood is a life-giving source to a body, but it needs a body to make it alive.

17:19.789 --> 17:24.156
The blood makes that body that needs that blood alive.

17:26.099 --> 17:26.479
You with me?

17:27.301 --> 17:28.903
I mean, it's not real complicated.

17:28.943 --> 17:31.467
Shall we say rocket science?

17:32.488 --> 17:33.770
But I want to tell you something.

17:34.672 --> 17:38.898
When blood goes into a body, it helps that body come back alive

17:39.106 --> 17:42.991
when we're low on blood and we need a transfusion or platelets or anything like that.

17:44.533 --> 17:52.623
But the thing about it is, is God, when he works in us, he doesn't repair what's broken.

17:54.085 --> 17:55.066
He makes it brand new.

17:58.430 --> 17:59.612
Think about that for a second.

17:59.912 --> 18:03.637
He doesn't patch us up our sin and say, oh, look, it's all covered up.

18:03.677 --> 18:04.638
You can't see it anymore.

18:05.099 --> 18:07.762
There's a patch there and we all know it.

18:09.026 --> 18:11.028
I was embarrassed to have patches on.

18:11.088 --> 18:19.897
You know, I don't know if you'll remember these patches, but if you didn't iron them right, even if you did, that'd peel off.

18:21.458 --> 18:26.243
I had patches, sometimes two and three patch on my pants, halfway on and halfway on.

18:26.263 --> 18:27.905
It was worse to have them.

18:27.925 --> 18:30.988
And when you say, well, I'm done with this and you peel it off, the hole's bigger.

18:32.349 --> 18:34.792
See God, God isn't going to just patch something.

18:34.832 --> 18:37.234
Oh, look, there's that patch over the sin.

18:37.986 --> 18:40.610
Because it reminds you, there's still sin, it's covering.

18:40.650 --> 18:43.574
So the covering of what God did in the Old Testament doesn't work for us.

18:44.255 --> 18:46.198
It wasn't a completed work.

18:46.578 --> 18:47.700
It was a cover over.

18:48.762 --> 18:50.945
We needed something new to come out of it.

18:51.265 --> 18:53.368
And Jesus says, my blood is a new covenant.

18:55.852 --> 18:59.697
Not an old covenant, the way it used to be, but new.

19:02.161 --> 19:05.746
So God, when he makes something brand new, he makes it holy.

19:06.626 --> 19:10.711
And the only way it can be holy is if it's pure and undefiled.

19:10.751 --> 19:15.537
Think of it like this.

19:16.418 --> 19:18.020
Scripture tells us over and over again.

19:18.861 --> 19:21.284
There is nothing unholy in the presence of God.

19:23.166 --> 19:26.370
You can't look on God's face and live because we are unholy.

19:27.151 --> 19:33.298
Moses couldn't and he was probably at that time the most righteous man around, but God still wouldn't let him look at his face.

19:33.826 --> 19:52.687
because he even told Moses, no man shall look at my face and live because unrighteousness cannot stand in the presence of God's glory and holiness because it consumes what's unjust and unrighteous and what's not unjust is what's righteous and that's what remains and we are sinners.

19:53.869 --> 20:02.258
So the holiness and glory and power of God would obliterate us and that's just how it is because God's holiness

20:02.338 --> 20:05.285
will not allow anything unrighteous in its presence.

20:06.808 --> 20:14.124
So when God wants to give us the lifeblood of Jesus, we need a body that's going to hold holiness.

20:16.470 --> 20:20.178
We need something holy to house what's holy.

