23:01.168 --> 23:02.930
That also happens to be

23:03.234 --> 23:04.456
the body of Christ.

23:08.182 --> 23:13.770
You say, well, faster than does that mean when you took me in the day, you sinned?

23:15.352 --> 23:15.613
No.

23:17.175 --> 23:18.818
No, because it's symbolic.

23:21.141 --> 23:22.824
It's remembering what he's done.

23:23.365 --> 23:32.178
So when I took the juice first, it was being recognized in a body that was already transformed spiritually.

23:33.474 --> 23:37.458
The wafer just reminded me of that process in reverse order.

23:39.880 --> 23:48.950
So I wanted you to know that the physical elements order doesn't matter what actually happens spiritually does.

23:50.952 --> 23:52.173
Absolutely matters.

23:53.775 --> 24:01.202
Being remade and remolded into something brand new requires us to have a spiritual body, the house, the Holy Spirit,

24:01.474 --> 24:04.739
our Heavenly Father and His beloved Son, Jesus Christ.

24:05.220 --> 24:07.463
They will not dwell in something unholy.

24:07.903 --> 24:19.060
Yet, John 14 tells us that the Father and the Son, if we love others as Jesus has loved us and keep His commandments, He and the Father will come and make their home in us.

24:19.641 --> 24:23.466
They can't make their home in us if we're unholy.

24:23.847 --> 24:31.378
But if we love us others, as He has loved us and we keep His commandments, we are walking in righteousness and they can dwell in us.

24:32.738 --> 24:44.857
We are holy when we do those things because God has made us clean and new by washing us and making us new creations spiritually.

24:46.640 --> 24:51.528
So God comes in and dwells in us and makes us holy.

24:53.671 --> 24:56.195
If we were unholy, God couldn't come in.

24:56.235 --> 25:00.722
We'd disintegrate because we're in the presence of God's all-powerful mighty

25:00.802 --> 25:02.926
righteousness as ungodly people.

25:07.333 --> 25:15.207
Communion is the outward sign of the actuality of God's recreating work in us.

25:16.930 --> 25:18.412
It's exactly what communion is.

25:18.553 --> 25:19.234
I'll say it again.

25:19.294 --> 25:26.386
Communion is the outward sign of the actuality of God's recreating work in you and me.

25:28.290 --> 25:36.180
During communion, we agree with what Jesus said and remember what he did and why.

25:36.220 --> 25:54.642
In 1 Corinthians chapter 11, the institution of holy communion that we use, in verses 23 through 26, we hear this and you hear me say this every first Sunday or as often as we do communion.

25:57.282 --> 26:07.293
The Lord Jesus on the same night when she was betrayed took bread and when he had given things he broke it and said, take eat this is my body which is broken for you do this in remembrance of me.

26:07.333 --> 26:16.983
In the same manner he also took the cup after supper saying this cup is a new covenant in my blood this do as often as you drink it in remembrance of me.

26:17.384 --> 26:27.154
Verse 26, for as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup you proclaim the Lord's death

26:28.642 --> 26:29.803
until he comes.

26:32.166 --> 26:33.507
You proclaim his death.

26:34.148 --> 26:37.232
What's his death but us getting his body?

26:37.272 --> 26:42.617
And when we get his body, we can receive his blood.

26:43.018 --> 26:47.263
What good is us being the body of Christ without the lifeblood in it?

26:48.504 --> 26:48.764
Right?

26:49.185 --> 26:49.745
We need that.

26:51.587 --> 26:54.871
So we are now new creations in Jesus Christ.

26:56.132 --> 26:57.554
We have his

26:57.666 --> 27:04.175
lifeblood in us made possible because of his death and resurrection.

27:05.937 --> 27:08.741
You are brand new because of that.

27:08.781 --> 27:19.997
Now we have to learn how to renew our mind, to understand our spiritual place and the reality of who he has made us to be brand new.

27:21.238 --> 27:22.400
We are not who we were.

27:22.941 --> 27:24.403
We are who he says we are.

27:24.883 --> 27:26.866
We have to figure that out with himself.

27:28.194 --> 27:31.298
The temptationists believe that this didn't really happen.

27:32.400 --> 27:33.501
That's the temptation.

27:34.482 --> 27:44.575
As after all, we are the same people we've always been, still in the same body, still the same mind, still the blood running through our body, but that's just the physical reality of your life.

27:46.298 --> 27:55.730
But this is why Jesus said, as often as you do this, remember what I've done for you, because we keep forgetting.

27:58.242 --> 27:59.784
We need that reminder, don't we?

28:01.066 --> 28:07.856
So when I took and asked God, why does it matter or does it matter?

28:07.936 --> 28:10.640
The bread or the juices first.

28:10.660 --> 28:11.421
Here's what he said.

28:12.643 --> 28:17.029
You can't put the new blood into the old body.

28:18.050 --> 28:26.322
So I'm going to give you a new body and then the blood can come into your new body and you'll be holy and righteous filled with Christ's life blood.

28:26.882 --> 28:32.471
And at that moment, I understood you can't put new wine into an old wine skin.

28:32.771 --> 28:35.536
You have to be a new creation to receive blood of Christ.

28:36.217 --> 28:37.359
It's all symbolic.

28:37.379 --> 28:41.365
It's all connected and it's all scriptural that the life is in the blood.

28:41.706 --> 28:46.494
And if you want the life of Christ, you have to have his body and be his body.

28:47.495 --> 28:54.226
So he can put his life blood into you because he can't put holy life blood into you until your body is his.

28:56.482 --> 28:57.103
That makes sense.

28:58.285 --> 28:59.146
And that's what he showed me.

28:59.186 --> 29:08.602
And all of a sudden, the patch made sense and the fasting made sense and the blood and the wine and the wines can all be in the same reference.

29:09.203 --> 29:11.607
But Jesus used parables.

29:13.230 --> 29:14.412
So we think about them.

29:14.772 --> 29:17.497
It only took me 45 years to figure that one out.

29:18.719 --> 29:19.600
Something like that.

29:21.884 --> 29:23.186
But maybe longer.

29:23.554 --> 29:24.756
Probably longer than that.

29:24.956 --> 29:26.839
I was thinking I was 51, but I'm 61.

29:28.401 --> 29:28.742
Goodness.

29:29.202 --> 29:31.165
Probably 55 years to figure that one out.

29:31.726 --> 29:37.795
But you got it this morning from a revelation of God finally clarifying.

29:38.556 --> 29:39.137
Did you know?

29:39.197 --> 29:46.328
Did you know you have a spiritual body right now that his life blood flows through when you belong to him?

29:47.189 --> 29:48.992
Did you know he's pleased to dwell in you?

29:49.373 --> 29:52.978
And he brought the father with him and all he asks is that you follow him.

29:53.058 --> 29:55.622
love as he loves and do what he asks.

29:56.283 --> 29:57.405
That's all you have to do.

29:58.286 --> 30:05.357
And during Lent, it's a time of coming humbly before God and saying, help me to live out this life you've called me to.

30:06.018 --> 30:12.528
I repent when I've listened to the old body and the old blood, which says, I am what I used to be.

30:13.249 --> 30:15.412
Instead of who you say, I am brand new in Christ.

30:16.474 --> 30:18.477
You are brand new in Christ.

30:18.597 --> 30:22.002
And Jesus says, as often as you take communion,

30:22.210 --> 30:23.392
Remember what I've done for you.

30:25.395 --> 30:26.457
Jesus did that for you.

30:26.958 --> 30:30.143
Praise His holy name because we couldn't do it for ourselves.

30:30.583 --> 30:33.388
We could just stick a patchwork on and make it worse.

30:35.171 --> 30:35.892
Would you pray with me?

30:37.835 --> 30:43.203
Heavenly Father, thank you for your word this morning that you have given us a new body.

30:43.243 --> 30:43.824
Thank you.

30:43.864 --> 30:49.874
Sometimes this old one just, we're waiting to see the full manifestation of the spiritual one.

30:51.010 --> 31:01.003
But thank you that you've given us a new body and you've given your life blood in us that we would know in our spirit with witness to your spirit that we belong to you, that we are yours.

31:02.005 --> 31:08.313
And that which is outward is wasting away, but that which is inward, as Paul says, is being renewed every day.

31:10.015 --> 31:16.925
So renew us with your mind, your heart, and with your blood.

31:18.266 --> 31:21.010
And as we commune today, Heavenly Father, commune with us,

31:21.890 --> 31:23.124
I pray this in the name of Jesus.

31:23.832 --> 31:24.338
Amen.

